					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-7942260#post-4060197</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-7942260/alexandria-burning#post-4060197</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 16 Nov 2018 14:45:59 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Judge_Dreddpool</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2984376</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>SCP-4001 became my #1 favourite SCP after I discovered it today.</p> <p>This tale became the 2nd best Tale I have ever read, surpassing <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/the-king-is-dead">The King Is Dead</a>, <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/scp-foundation-the-movie">SCP Foundation: The Movie</a> &amp; <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/how-173-got-to-site-19">How 173 Got to Site-19</a> (Still doesn't surpass <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/incident-239-b-clef-kondraki">Incident 239-B - Clef Kondraki</a>) in my top fives Tales.</p> <p>For added feels, I listened to this <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Llf6t6KgQqY">iconic theme</a> whilst reading. Let's just say that listening to Tears in Rain while reading a potential tear-inducing tale is kinda a bad idea.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
